"""v2-S04 Stage D iter 5 — clumped K≥5 constellation with LOO drop-lift.

User correction (2026-04-28):
- Manual landmark constellations are typically CLUMPED in a local volume,
  not spread.  Drop the prior pairwise-spread + hull-area gates entirely.
- Validity of each anchor is judged by LOCAL LOO drop-lift (how much
  removing the anchor degrades the local fit), NOT global aniso-similarity
  RMSE.
- Use K≥5 to give the warp enough constraints.
- All evaluation is done within the local volume of the constellation.

Choice of warp model
--------------------
The manual analogue is TPS, but in 3D with K=5 anchors thin-plate-spline
has 15 DOF / 15 obs / 0 residual DOF and wildly extrapolates outside the
control hull (a quick test gave mean residuals of 10³–10⁴ µm on test
cells inside a 200 µm margin).  Aniso-similarity (9 DOF / 15 obs /
6 residual DOF) is the honest stable model for K=5: it's the v1
landmark transform, it does not explode in extrapolation, and LOO with
K-1=4 anchors is still determined (3 residual DOF).

Dedupe rule
-----------
Two CZ in the same clump can have the same rank-1 HCR (they're nearby
and gating is loose).  We dedupe by promoting to the next-rank HCR
when a collision occurs in clump assembly.

Pipeline
--------
1. Per subject, take top-slab candidates from step 1.
2. Per-CZ ranked HCR list (sorted by rank).  Rank CZ by total
   candidate score.
3. Enumerate clumped K constellations: for each seed CZ in the top-T,
   take its K-1 nearest CZ neighbours (in cz_warp xyz space).  For
   HCR assignment, walk the per-CZ rank list and skip HCRs already
   used in this clump.
4. For each constellation:
   a. Fit aniso-similarity (R, scales, src_mean, dst_mean) on the K
      (CZ_xyz → HCR_xyz) anchor pairs.
   b. Local volume = bbox of CZ anchors + margin (xy 200 µm, z 100 µm).
   c. Test set = top-slab CZ inside the local volume that are NOT
      among the K anchors and have at least one candidate.
   d. d_full = mean NN distance from warped(test_cz_xyz) to nearest
      HCR_GFP+ centroid (whole-subject HCR pool).
   e. For each anchor i (LOO):
        Refit on K-1 anchors;
        d_loo_i = mean NN distance over the same test set;
        drop_lift_i = d_loo_i - d_full   [positive = anchor i helps].
   f. Pass = (drop_lift_i > TAU) for all i; score = min_i drop_lift_i.

Outputs
-------
- ``step2c_{sid}{TAG}_clumped.csv``        — per-constellation rows
- ``step2c_all_subjects_summary{TAG}.csv`` — best per subject
"""
